      <tr>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Zaar</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I'm having issues getting to sleep and bored to tears of getting AA atm so figured I'd do a small write up on how we can be effective at certain raids without twitching. This is mainly from a personal perspective so critique at will.</P><P>I figured I'd just pick some higher level raid mobs and tell you what myself and the other necro's do at raids.</P><P><b>Basement Cursed Cycle</b></P><P>- Dots of course on all 3. Can rotate certain dots with other necro's present.<BR>- Charm skellies from the mines with Thrall if you're brave.<BR>- Group with the mages / clerics and do group taps for when they rod, in combination with a GCH cleric this is quite effective.<BR>- For cursed if you have a group of 4 strong melee, 1 GCH cleric and a necro for group tap, that group can basically stay fighting the cursed the whole time without having to weave the dot.<BR>- Group with 5 wiz / nukers and mind wrack the cursed, while this is still kinda twitching it's not too bad.</P><P><b>High Priest</b></P><P>- Dots of course, can cycle them.<BR>- Banish the 4 named disiples.<BR>- Charm the disiples and use them against the High Priest. Usually we have 2 necro's and when the first pull comes, we banish 2, charm 2. Thus splitting the respawn even tho sometimes it's borked anyways. If the charm breaks you'll usually get summoned but they like to cast, so you can usually just channel another charm and back up to the wall.<BR>- Mind wrack / group tap same as cursed cycle.</P><P><b>Emperor Ssra</b></P><P>- Steal rods and chain Gang Touch!<BR>- Make a pet ( pets are HUGE in the emp fight )<BR>- Funeral Pyre, Ignite Blood, Pyrocuror, Plague<BR>- Drag corpses ( If people are dying )<BR>- Rez people in if you short on Clerics and some momo has been begging for a rez for 10 mins and he's a warrior with AE taunt up.</P><P><b>Arch Lich</b></P><P>- Chain Exile, that is all. We're wizards in this fight, drop the odd vex to fight the dot unless you're weaving.<BR>- Group with people and keep group tap up to fight the dot.<BR>- All dots stick for the most part, but if you have fury 3, chain exile imo!</P><P><b>Vex Thal</b></P><P>- Summon the raid after you wipe.<BR>- Help uhm, move the raid around.<BR>- Pull ( while this may sound stupid, if you have no monks necro can pull just fine for the most part )<BR>- On all bosses all dots land, pets are HUGE in all boss fights.<BR>- Lifeburn is very useful in tight situations when you need to drop a mob NOW.</P><P><b>Avatar of war</b></P><P>- Pick up rods, run out of range where no one can see you use it then chain ToN.<BR>- Make a pet, but back it off until all dire charm pets are in. If a DC backs off, back off your pet then send it in again once DC is back in.<BR>- Use Chill bones when he's at a sliver of health and scream "HE GATED"</P><P>For all raids there are things we do effectively that revolve around prep etc. Of course we always can save the raid in case of wipeout. We can train shit away with our DA's, we can drag mage corpses with DA. We can levant to set up CoH. We can pull with a mixture of spells and abilities we have. We can if we want feed I guess, personally none of us do under normal circumstances, but we're not stupid. If we need someone to have mana NOW we will feed.</P><P>Anyways just some food for thought, like I said can't sleep figured I'd see if I could post something usefull. I'm sure many of you can think of other things to do at these raids, I just posted what I do for the most part.</P><P>Zaar Deth'Mortis<BR>Leader of Triton<BR><a href="http://www.tritonguild.com" target="_blank">http://www.tritonguild.com</a><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43499</a><BR>"Please go back to your fantasy playstyle and leave the real necromancers alone." - Potus</font></td>
